The mysterious death of a 25-year old University of Michigan medical student last Wednesday is being treated as a homicide as friends remember him as a would-be surgeon who 'would have cured cancer'.

Paul DeWolf was discovered dead from a gunshot wound in his own bedroom at a university fraternity house on the 200 block of North Ingalls Street he shared with other medical students in Ann Arbor, Michigan.

His room was neat and tidy and no valuables had been removed when his body was found at around 11 p.m. - and so far no suspects have been named and no weapon found.

