Following the murder investigation, the University of Michigan has increased campus patrols and warned students that a killer may be on the loose.

The university is taking 'all necessary steps to assure the safety of the campus community,' said University of Michigan President Mary Sue Coleman to ABC News.

At his home in Western Michigan, DeWolf's loved ones spoke to ABC News of their utter disbelief that the aspiring surgeon has apparently been killed.

'He had such big aspirations for life,' DeWolf's friend Sarala Sarah said. 'He's the type of person who would have cured cancer.'

